Certainly! Here is a step-by-step guide to ensure your butterfly image appears correctly on the website by adding the necessary information to your JSON data:

### Step 1: Identify the Missing Information
To display an image correctly, you typically need the following information:
- Image URL
- Image width
- Image height
- Alternative text (alt text) for accessibility

### Step 2: Update Your JSON Data
Ensure your JSON data includes all the necessary fields. Here is an example of how your JSON data should look:

```json
{
  "image": {
    "url": "https://example.com/butterfly.jpg",
    "width": 600,
    "height": 400,
    "alt": "A beautiful butterfly"
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Modify Your HTML and JavaScript
Ensure your HTML and JavaScript are set up to read the JSON data and display the image correctly.

#### HTML
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Butterfly Image</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="image-container"></div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

